    Further, it does clarify the status of a ludic pattern ‚Äî what you call a game ‚Äî as something that can be run entiely in one‚Äôs head, or be designed on the fly or as a folk process, which is something a lot of people don‚Äôt grasp.

    For your purposes, all it means is that what you currently call game becomes a new word. I propose Lude.
